args:
After Farren repels the wyrmbound soldiers,
Jake suddenly appears to bar his way and
reveals he is now a candidate for promotion
within the Syndicate. After meeting with a
crushing defeat, Grace advises Farren to think
about the reasons for why he fights.
Madness! How could we be defeated by\na failure like him?!
*pant* *pant* How's that feel?\nNow if you agree to get out of the village\nand never come back, I'll let you go.
Less a failure and more an irregularity...\nI can see why our researchers were so\ninterested in you.
I don't know who you are, but if you think\nyou're gonna hurt anyone else, you can...\nWhat?!
And kicking. Seems like Lady Luck hasn't\ngotten tired of me just yet.
So what about Aldred?! Is he okay?!
Oh, I can fill you in on all of that...\nbut there are going to be some conditions.
I need you to come with me, Farren.\nThe Syndicate has a tremendous amount\nof interest in your irregular powers.
I give you my word you won't be treated as\na traitor, but instead welcomed back as a\nlike-minded comrade.
So you want me to join the Syndicate?
That's right. C'mon, don't you want to be\npart of the side that's in control for once?
No! I've chosen to PROTECT people from\nthe Syndicate!
Chose? You haven't chosen anything\nduring this entire process, little duck.
Ah, well. If you're going to refuse our most\ngenerous offer, we'll just have to treat you\nas the traitor you are.
Jake, stop! You don't have to do this!
Jake? I don't even know that name\nanymore...for I have been reborn\nin the light of the Syndicate!

I am a candidate to join the upper
echelons of the Syndicate, and I am he
who controls the wyrmbound. From this
point forth, you can call me...the Captain!
Get your damn head out of the clouds!\nHe's coming for us!
Hrk... S-stop this, Jake!\nI don't want to fight you!
You're still far too soft, little duck. How are\nyou supposed to protect anyone else's life\nwhen you can't even protect your own?!
Focus, Farren! I ain't lookin' to eat dirt\ntoday just because you can't get your\ncrap together!
Your B-Unit is incredibly chatty! I wonder\nif his formation of an ego is the cause of\nthe irregularity?
The eggheads back at HQ will be veeery\nhappy if I bring that B-Unit back with me,\nwhich means you need to go down!

Heh. My wyrmbinding has been designed
for use by the Syndicate elite, and it 
clearly dwarfs the power of a pathetic
little irregular like you.
Get your damn hands off me, bucko!
No, Jake! Let Lil' Barb go!
Sadly, I've no more use for you now that I\nhave the B-Unit—so you and that faithless\nresearcher can go ahead and die together.
Leave the rest to us, Captain.
See that you finish them. No mistakes.
...I'll buy you some time, Grace.\nYou get out of here.
Ha ha ha! How the hell are you going to\nbuy anyone time when you don't even\nhave your shell anymore?!

Sealed wyrms steeped in fury!
Dragons cursed by fate!
Break free of the chains that bind you
and unleash your wrathful cries!
What the? My arm's movin' on its own...\nI feel something inside me! GYAAAAAA!

The wyrmbinding has gone out of control...
But that shouldn't be possible for non-
fusion types like us! How have you done
this, you traitors?!
Forgive me. I did not want to resort to this,\nbut our situation is terrifically desperate.\nNow, Farren! Run!
There's nothing you can do here\nexcept perish. Now run!
This is where our ways must part, Farren.\nReturn to the Halidom.
Because I've realized that I can't make you\nfight anymore.
Why, because I lost Lil' Barb?

I know I don't have the power I used to
anymore, but I can still be plenty useful!
Heck, just use me as a shield to protect
someone else if you want!
That mindset is exactly why I can't make\nyou keep fighting—you aren't considerate\nenough of your own well-being.
Look, I'm sorry if that makes you worry\nabout me, but it's a price I'm willing to\npay if it lets me save someone.
But you don't just want to save someone,\nFarren—you want to sacrifice yourself\nin the process.
You have survivor's guilt over the fact you\nare alive due to the sacrifice of others.
So now you are looking to die in someone\nelse's place in order to relieve that guilt.
I know this because it is a feeling to which\nI am very much attuned, for I also once\nyearned for death.
In any event, I can't take you with me into\nthe jaws of the enemy as you are now.

If you are going to continue battling the
Syndicate, you need to sit down and think
about your true reasons for fighting—
and for living.
